{"author":{"id":"138b13306404778af60b1d60d606624fec41556ddac480b2d5f762806ce84fed"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1783043942,"nonce":"LN8KavEnXowTHSwjbpfAp0TuBYA=","kind":"spec","title":"`edited` timestamp + sort-direction ruling — design spec","content_type":"text/markdown"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1783043942,"nonce":"MVT1kNE0ldjpohApdJLx+SV9nlo=","body":"# `edited` timestamp + sort-direction ruling — design spec\n\n**Status:** draft for review\n**Date:** 2026-07-03\n**TODO items cleared:** two \"Quick sort rulings\" from `kref show 81be409e4ef8`\n(the `--sort edited` item and the `--asc`/`--desc`-vs-`:desc` item).\n\n## Summary\n\nTwo small, coupled decisions about `kref list`/`kref search` ordering:\n\n1. **`edited` is a new, distinct timestamp** — not a synonym for `updated`. It\n   records when an entry's *body* last changed, independent of metadata churn\n   (labels, links, status, retier). It becomes a sortable key, a `--columns`\n   column, and the **new default sort for `kref list`** (`edited:desc`).\n2. **Direction stays the `:desc` suffix.** No `--asc`/`--desc` flags are added.\n\nBoth decisions follow kref's \"one name per concept\" ethos: `edited` earns its\nplace by meaning something `updated` does not, and direction keeps a single\nmechanism rather than two overlapping ones.\n\n## Motivation\n\n`updated` bumps on *every* operation — add a label, add a link, change status,\nretier, or edit the body. When triaging \"what documents actually changed\nrecently,\" that metadata churn is noise. LLM-driven workflows label and link\nentries constantly, so `updated` recency is dominated by bookkeeping.\n\n`edited` answers the sharper question: *when did this document's prose last\nchange?* This is the filesystem `ctime` vs content-`mtime` distinction, applied\nto entries.\n\n## The three-timestamp model\n\n| Field     | Meaning                        | Bumped by        |\n|-----------|--------------------------------|------------------|\n| `created` | entry came into being          | `Create`         |\n| `edited`  | **body/prose** last changed    | `SetBody` only   |\n| `updated` | **anything** last changed      | every operation  |\n\nAt birth, `edited == created` (creation is `Create` + `SetBody`, see\n`internal/store/store.go:219-223`). They diverge on the first later body edit.\n`updated` diverges from `edited` on the first metadata-only op.\n\n## Why this is clean to implement\n\n- **`Compile` folds ops in order** (`internal/entry/entry.go:48`) and **only\n  `SetBody` writes the body.** So a new `EditedAt` field set *inside*\n  `SetBody.Apply` automatically holds the time of the last body edit — no\n  op-log walk, exactly mirroring how `UpdatedAt` already works, narrowed to one\n  op type.\n- **Zero migration.** Snapshots are recompiled on every read, and existing\n  entries' histories already contain `SetBody` ops, so `edited` derives\n  retroactively and correctly for all current entries.\n- **Additive JSON.** `Snapshot` gains an `edited_at` field; no existing field\n  changes shape.\n\n## Changes\n\n### 1. Snapshot (`internal/entry/snapshot.go`)\n\nAdd:\n\n```go\nEditedAt time.Time `json:\"edited_at\"` // last body-edit time (SetBody); falls back to CreatedAt when the body was never set\n```\n\n### 2. `SetBody.Apply` (`internal/entry/operations.go`)\n\n```go\nfunc (op *SetBody) Apply(s *Snapshot) {\n\ts.Body = op.Body\n\ts.EditedAt = op.Time()\n\ts.UpdatedAt = op.Time()\n}\n```\n\nNo other op touches `EditedAt`.\n\n### 3. Zero-body fallback\n\nAn entry created with an empty body (a `Create` with no following `SetBody`)\nhas a zero `EditedAt`. Resolve this in `Compile` after the fold: if\n`snap.EditedAt.IsZero()`, set `snap.EditedAt = snap.CreatedAt`. This keeps the\nfield always-populated so sort and render never see a zero time, and reads\nnaturally (\"its content dates from when it was created\").\n\n### 4. Render column (`internal/render/render.go`)\n\n- New `ColEdited Column = \"edited\"`.\n- Add to `AllColumns` (after `ColUpdated`).\n- Header: `columnHeaders[ColEdited] = \"EDITED\"`.\n- Description: `\"last body-edit date (YYYY-MM-DD)\"`.\n- Add to `sortableColumns` (after `ColUpdated`).\n- `snapLess` case `ColEdited`: `return a.EditedAt.Before(b.EditedAt)`.\n- `sortDefaultsDesc`: include `ColEdited` (it is a date field, so a bare\n  `--sort edited` sorts newest-first).\n\n### 5. Default sort\n\nChange `kref list`'s default `--sort` from `updated` to `edited`. `kref search`\nkeeps its `matches:desc` default (relevance, not recency).\n\n### 6. Wide view (`WideColumns`)\n\n`WideColumns` today shows `updated`. Since `edited` is now the primary recency\nsignal and the default sort key, `WideColumns` shows `edited` in place of\n`updated` (keeps the wide view at 7 columns; the sort key stays visible).\n`updated` remains reachable via explicit `--columns`.\n\n### 7. Direction: no change\n\n`--sort key:asc` / `key:desc` stays the sole direction mechanism. No\n`--asc`/`--desc` flags. Rationale: a suffix co-locates direction with the field\n(surviving a future multi-key sort), avoids a two-mechanisms precedence rule,\nand does not collide with `search`'s `matches:desc` default.\n\n## Non-goals\n\n- No rename of `updated` (the column, header, or `updated_at` JSON field).\n- No `--asc`/`--desc` flags.\n- No change to `search`'s default sort.\n- No new op type — `edited` is derived from existing `SetBody` ops.\n\n## Testing\n\n- **Unit (`operations_test.go`):** a `SetBody` sets `EditedAt`; a later\n  `AddLabel` bumps `UpdatedAt` but leaves `EditedAt` unchanged; an entry with no\n  `SetBody` compiles to `EditedAt == CreatedAt`.\n- **Unit (`render_test.go`):** `ColEdited` is in `AllColumns`, `sortableColumns`,\n  has a header and description (the registry-consistency specs already enforce\n  coverage, so this is mostly automatic once the maps are populated);\n  `snapLess` orders by `EditedAt`; a bare `--sort edited` yields\n  `SortSpec{Key: ColEdited, Desc: true}`.\n- **E2E:** create an entry, add a label, assert `list` (now `edited:desc`)\n  does *not* reorder on the label-only change, while `--sort updated` does;\n  assert `--columns edited` renders an `EDITED` column; assert `--json` carries\n  `edited_at`.\n\n## Backward compatibility\n\n- JSON consumers gain `edited_at`; nothing is removed or reshaped.\n- `kref list` output order changes for stores where entries have had\n  metadata-only ops after their last body edit (they will sort by body-edit\n  time instead of any-change time). Pre-release, so acceptable and intended.\n- `--sort updated` remains available for the old behavior."},{"type":11,"timestamp":1783043942,"nonce":"JuhodetkC7B8SyDY/UZxTetRuKg=","actor":"Trevor Vaughan","actor_kind":"human","source_path":"docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-03-edited-timestamp-and-sort-vocabulary-design.md","trigger":"ingest"},{"type":11,"timestamp":1783133414,"nonce":"DauEHZ8ZoWlqYZ0P0JL6U3PlYL8=","actor":"Trevor Vaughan","actor_kind":"human","source_path":"","trigger":"retier"}]}